          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CreateFiscalYearPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to calculate and return a specific fiscal year period based on the input parameters. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used for computations or transformations that can be expressed as a single value output."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level is considered medium due to the potential intricacies involved in calculating fiscal periods, which may include conditional logic and date manipulations. The function's complexity is also influenced by the need to handle various fiscal year definitions and edge cases."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@Date (DATETIME/DATE)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter represents the date for which the fiscal year period needs to be calculated. It is the primary input that determines the fiscal period based on the organization's fiscal calendar."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@FiscalYearStartMonth (INT)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter specifies the starting month of the fiscal year. It is crucial for determining the fiscal year boundaries and calculating the correct fiscal period."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
